Thirdly, But Fox goes on;
the Prieſts and Presbyterians cry up an Earthly King, and will have Ceſar.
                   The Quarrel you ſee, is againſt an Earthly King, not againſt a wicked perſecuring one, or elſe he muſt make them the ſame; and ſo all Earthly Kings are Nero's and Diocleſians.
